Reasoning: The paper proposes a new conceptual foundation for the notion of information based on distinction graphs and graphtropy. It discusses connections between graphtropy and thermodynamic and quantum entropy, as well as the semantics of the Second Law of Thermodynamics and the Maximum Entropy Production Principle. It also introduces a novel computational model called Dynamic Distinction Graphs. Based on these topics, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
